{
  "texts": [
    "Some authors claim that the morphology and function of organoids are sufficient to exclude the presence of consciousness (Lunshof, 2020).",
    "However, their anticipated future abilities raise concerns about possible moral considerability emerging during research, necessitating ethical oversight (Owen et al., 2023).",
    "Of course, possession of human neurons alone does not confer moral status.",
    "The developmental context matters (Farahany et al.,).",
    "In contrast to natural embryological development, cerebral organoids are artificially engineered from stem cells."
  ]
}